The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically the concept of treewidth sparsifiers. This topic falls under several sub-categories in arXiv CS, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Given that the paper focuses on the treewidth of graphs and the algorithmic construction of sparsifiers, it is most likely to be classified under cs.DM and cs.DS. However, the paper also involves the study of minors and routing on node-disjoint paths, which are topics that fall under cs.CG and cs.GT. Finally, the paper's discussion of the complexity of treewidth sparsifiers and the fact that it contradicts a known result in the field suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.CC.
